Package :
Package is mechanism to group related classes,interfaces and enmus into a single module.
syntax : package <package-name>
They are categorized into two types
              -- User defined packages
              -- Built in packages(lang,util) 

packages are used to prevent naming conflicts,controlled access and makes searching and locating the files easier
Generally it will be first statement in the file.
For importing package : import <package-name>
Example:

MyPackage.java

package mypackage;
import java.util.*;

class MyPackage
{
public static void main(String args[])
{
java.lang.String str="Chinmay";
System.out.println(str);
}
}